// ============================================================================
// Geometry OS - Simple RISC-V Test Program (Output "GEOM")
// ============================================================================
//
// This is a simple test guest program that writes "GEOM" to UART.
// It's used to verify the RISC-V emulator works correctly.
//
// Memory Layout:
// 0x14000: Guest PC
// 0x14100: Guest Registers (x0-x31)
// 0x18000: Guest RAM (this program)
// 0x00200: UART Output
// ============================================================================

// RISC-V program that outputs "GEOM" using STORE instructions
// Format: SW rs2, imm(rs1) - Store word from rs2 to memory[rs1+imm]

// We'll use x1 as UART pointer and x2-x5 for the characters

// LUI x1, 0x00000 - Load upper immediate (x1 = 0x00000000)
// Then ADDI x1, x1, 0x200 to get UART address

// Actually, let's use a simpler approach:
// ADDI x1, x0, 0x200 would need to sign-extend, but 0x200 > 12 bits
// So we use LUI + ADDI

// LUI x1, 0x00000 (x1 = 0)
// 0x00000037

// ADDI x1, x1, 0x200 (x1 = 0x200 = UART)
// 0x20010093

// ADDI x2, x0, 0x47 (x2 = 'G' = 0x47 = 71)
// 0x04700113

// SW x2, 0(x1) - Store 'G' to UART
// 0x00209023

// ADDI x2, x0, 0x45 (x2 = 'E' = 0x45 = 69)
// 0x04500113

// SW x2, 4(x1) - Store 'E' to UART+4
// 0x00209223

// ADDI x2, x0, 0x4F (x2 = 'O' = 0x4F = 79)
// 0x04F00113

// SW x2, 8(x1) - Store 'O' to UART+8
// 0x00209423

// ADDI x2, x0, 0x4D (x2 = 'M' = 0x4D = 77)
// 0x04D00113

// SW x2, 12(x1) - Store 'M' to UART+12
// 0x00209623

// EBREAK - Halt
// 0x00100073
